result.execSummary:
Jina May Pinc-Shaw was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jina May Pinc-Shaw was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Added to close case out only.

4:01 p.m. Jina M. Pinc-Shaw appears by video, in Custody, from Burnett County.  Assistant District Attorney Kevin Schmidt in Court.  Case on for Extradition Hearing (to Pine County, MN).  Defendant has signed waiver of extradition.  Court reviews rights with Defendant.  Defendant wishes to waive her right to hearing and return to State of MN voluntarily.  No threats or promises made to get her to sign.  Court will sign extradition paperwork.
